I've added some error handling which solves the problem on my machine.
In case that loading the cache file throws an exception the loadInstance() method in GlueIndex.java now throws an IOException which causes the glue index to build a new cache instead. Now a damaged cache file does not causes the whole g-Eclipse does not work anymore.

The change was just to add:
      } catch( Exception exception ) {
        throw new IOException("Could not load cache."); //$NON-NLS-1$
      }
to the existing try - catch in the method.

Since I don't know if this is autogenerated code (and therefore if this change will survive the next update), it would be nice if George could have a look at it and maybe integrate the change into the code generation.
